Okay, I admit I chose to watch this movie solely because I enjoy Dean Cane and his Mr Everyman persona. I have enjoyed his work in the past, (not counting the Saturday Movie of the week on the SciFi Channel.).  You know how it is... It's Dean Cane, not Jack Nicholson. You do know what your getting before you head down the rabbit hole.

Well oopsie daisy.  Although Cane is prominently featured on the Video poster for the movie. His performance is basically a walkon, and in my opinion he just phoned the performance in.

The premise for the tale had great potential but fell woefully short on quality of writing and characters as nuanced as a brick to the face.

Is it just me, or am I seeing a trend develop with the level of quality offered with the Prime membership.  It is beginning to appear that quality options are going to require additional monetary expendatures. I will have to rethink this membership benefit package.
